COMEDIAN, Skhumba Hlophe, allegedly left his fans high and dry on Thursday.He allegedly failed to pitch at Meat Lounge, in Sunninghill, Sandton.Fans were angry when they went to the venue for a fun night of comedy.A fan said: &ldquo;I&rsquo;d had a terrible week and was looking forward to laughing my stress off. We waited for hours, and by 10pm, people started to leave.&rdquo;Another source said: Skhumba should never forget where he comes from and never disappoint his fans. &ldquo;I thought he had a tragedy until I saw him posting about his upcoming show on social media.&rdquo;Meat Lounge&rsquo;s Thursday comedy nights have a big following. It&rsquo;s where the affluent unwind and network.Meat Lounge&rsquo;s manager, Michael Hlongwane&rsquo; confirmed Skhumba hasn&rsquo;t performed there for the last two months.&ldquo;Yesterday (Thursday) he didn&rsquo;t pitch and there was no communication at all. We&rsquo;ve suffered financially for the past two months as we&rsquo;d arranged everything and it cost us money. We&rsquo;ll still meet with my bosses to see if we can take legal action against him,&rdquo; he said.This week Skhumba said: &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t have a contract with Meat Lounge. I&rsquo;m one of the busiest comedians in Mzansi.&ldquo;It was an arrangement, and if they want publicity they mustn&rsquo;t use my name. Last month they booked someone when I was absent, why now?&ldquo;I&rsquo;m in Cape Town and I can&rsquo;t be in Meat Lounge just for fun. I&rsquo;m booked and getting more moola.&rdquo;